metadata.name: FXHASH Generative Logo #378
metadata.description:
Unique iteration of the first Generative Token minted on fxhash.

It also servers as the actual logo of the platform. It represents the generative processes driving fxhash tokens. Generative Tokens are fed with a unique hash to produce unique outputs based on the hash — they are functions with a hash as single input.

The growth that comes out of the text is driven by a "Dividing-Aggregating Walkers" (DAW) algorithm. The hash drives all the DAW settings, as well as a mutation factor which is responsible for changes in each Walker parameters as they divide.

Some iterations will produce very simple outputs whereas others might be more chaotic.

Piece by @ciphrd for fxhash

metadata.name: Neural Collapse #286
metadata.description:
What happens when your brain overloads, or when you lose control of your giant robot.

A study on the repetition and stacking of a simple but very dynamic structure.

Everything procedurally generated at runtime.
You can find more informations on the piece, its design and origins, here: https://ulucode.com/wp/neural-collapse/

Interactivity : 
- You can hover your mouse on the connectors to close them... temporarily
- Press and hold the mouse button to slightly move the viewpoint.

- Press "a" to increase quality of the antialiasing (3 levels), at the cost of performances. Especially useful on the palettes using outlines.
- Export a PNG capture at various resolutions by pressing the number keys 1 to 9 (top row or numpad, and only in live mode, after pressing "open"). Resolutions ranges from 720 to 7680 pixels. I recommend starting with "4".

GPU recommended. Best performances on Chrome in general.

Licensed under CC BY-NC-SA 4.0

metadata.name: Bellissimas #246
metadata.description:
Expressive portraits inspired by @michelepetrelli 

The used techniques search in the unexplored field of mixing pfp layer based work and real-time generative algorithms changing and adding to the premade assets.

The pre-generated assets include original artworks by Petrelli, Imitations of Petrelli's work by @brutalisti, GAN generated artworks inspired by Petrelli using several different AI technologies.

Every generatively chosen layer combination is live-processed and generatively altered in aspects of color and shape. Then the generative algorithm proceed with captured color palettes and generate background and additional drawing over and under the initial layers. The final result as acquired by visualizing everything with live generative algorithm that give additional layer of uniqueness.

Project by  @michelepetrelli & @brutalisti, curated by XCOLLABS

metadata.name: Euphonic #394
metadata.description:
Euphonic is an exploration of the emergent visual properties that arise from placing layers of simple lines atop one another.

In general this effect is called the Moiré effect. This effect really feels best in the tactile - when you have a printed page and an acetate sheet. This piece attempts to recreate that tactile joy.

This is built in WebGL 2 and so doesn't work in Safari 14 and below. All latest browsers will work as expected.

Licensing: BY-NC-ND see license.md for details.

metadata.name: FairyCells #343
metadata.description:
FairyCells is a series created by a generative system, displaying shapes, between 1 and 10, made up of three different color palettes. 
Cells cannot cross each other, and are composed of a flat tint and/or a hatch system.

You can right-click to download an SVG file of the NFT or press « E » to export as png (3401x3401px)

Moreover, the digital version can exist as a physical piece.
Owning the NFT gives the right to order, in addition, a 30x30cm plotter drawing of it. More information about it here: https://nft.julienespagnon.fr/fairy-cells.
You can see some test examples plotted in the google form: https://docs.google.com/forms/d/1FO3Umh49qmJApZAlQgZ46a2y421QYEWIW8r72nLrW4Q/edit

Work by Julien Espagnon - 2021/2022

metadata.name: 生成畫荷 #52
metadata.description:
It ain't hard to tell, code compiles, and then art reveals.

「天一生水，地六成之；地二生火，天七成之；天三生木，地八成之；地四生金，天九成之；天五生土，地十成之。天生地成，而行鬼神。」— 河圖

Heaven gens, earth erates, the acts of demons and gods, indefinitely, generate. 

荷花一現，河圖不見，生花成畫，心幸有憐。

I see that lotus, but this code does not render it. Flowers are generative, art is generative, and we feel. 

「自抒胸意，不襲前人；無人無我，無古無今」— 張大千七十七歲作

There is no I nor they, past or present. — Zhang Da Qian~1976

「墨落一時手不住，任譏老子做狂徒。」— 張大千八十四歲作

Oops! ink fell out of my hand. But, I, got it.  — Zhang Da Qian~1983

“We see things in things, 
then create and drop,
copyminters only look at commits, 
on github. 
Though they need not to peek,
my gen art’s free, to see, 
stuff on my mind, 
do not like, to be locked, in a file, 
it ain’t hard to smell.” — Zhang Da Qian x Nas x Jimi Wen

Press 1 to save png, only for Chrome, not Safari. Preview images are compressed.

License: CC BY-NC-ND 4.0

metadata.name: Morphology #78
metadata.description:
Spacebar to pause/unpause.

Fractals similar to Julia sets based on iterating the equation:

z(i+1) = a(i) * cos( b(i) *z(i) ) + c(i) *z^(-order) + d(i) 

With z(0) the canvas position, and the parameters a,b,c and d shifting over time and varying with each iteration.

Colour corresponds to the number of iterations before abs(Im(z)) or abs(Re(z)) > 100.

142 possible colour palettes!
